Fertility Journey:
How did we get here?
I got off birth control once Hunter & I got married in 2022 after 12 years on the pill. I quickly learned after 6 months of no period that something was up. I started gaining weight rapidly, so I went to my obgyn, then an endocrinologist & found out I had PCOS & wasn’t ovulating. My hormone levels were all out of whack. We started trying for a family last summer & realized I was going to need a little assistance. I was prescribed Metformin for PCOS & Chlomid/letrozole to help with ovulation & progesterone to get my period. After 3 months & no luck I went to a fertility clinic. PFCLA has been so wonderful & made this entire process a little bit easier. My doctor immediately started me on menopur & ovidrel. Hunter supported me in many ways throughout the entire process & gave me all my injections. After 3 months & no success (maybe a chemical pregnancy), we decided to do ivf! I know so many women struggle with fertility, I’m not alone & neither are you! I debated about waiting until I was pregnant (I’m optimistic it’ll happen!), but I wanted to share my experience in hopes to reach someone that is going through something similar or struggling with fertility. We do an egg retrieval in January & are praying for the best. I know it can be a long journey from here, but we are grateful for the opportunity to do ivf & expand our family. Stay tuned for our ivf journey! 🫶🏼

Are you sad or have you just not gotten a facial in a while? Beauty Heals! Thank you so much @drnathannewman for the best facial I’ve ever had! What a great way to spend a Friday right before the holidays. I’m so impressed with the science behind your skincare! I have issues with red/dry skin that is easily irritated or inflamed, so walking out of this facial with glowing, dewy skin was amazing. Happy Holidays, go get yourself the best facial, you deserve it!
Here we go 2024 🎉
